DESCRIPTION: Larva dark brown when alive; exuviae light brown, granulated, and hairless. Femora and tibiae ringed with pale and dark bands. Abdomen lanceolate with a complex color pattern (
Fig. 8
).

Abdomen. — Lanceolate (
Fig. 8
), finely granulose on dorsal and ventral surfaces, reaching its maximum width on abdominal segment 6 ; lateral margins of 2–9 with small spiniform setae, lateral margins of 6–9 ending in a robust spine, largest on 8 ; posterior margins of tergites 1–10 and postero-lateral margins of sternites 3–10 with a row of obtuse dark serrations that increase in size gradually from front to rear. Color pattern complex (
Fig. 8
). Female gonapophyses well developed (
Fig. 9
), reaching basal 0.3 to 0.5 of sternite 10 , median valvae slightly longer than lateral valvae, lateral valvae obtusely pointed and slightly convergent; median valvae parallel, sharply pointed. Caudal appendages (
Figs. 8–10
): cerci long ( Figs. 8, 10 ), tapering caudad, sharply pointed, internal margins, in dorsal view (
Figs. 10
a–b), sinuate, tips slightly convergent; yellowish brown on basal 0.80 , apical 0.20 reddish; surface covered with minute, scattered spiniform setae. Epiproct dark brown on basal 0.80 , apical 0.20 yellowish brown, parallel-sided, ending in two sharp, reddish points widely separated by a median U-shaped cleft ( Figs. 8, 10 a); dorsal margin carinate on apical 0.50 , covered with small, robust setae. Paraprocts pyramidal ( Figs. 9, 10 a), dorsal and internal margins serrate, serrations low and truncate; tips red, sharply pointed, very slightly convergent; external and ventral surfaces mostly yellowish brown, internal surface mostly dark brown, all surfaces covered with short, stiff setae, more abundant on internal surface. Average size proportions (lengths measured dorsally), with paraproct adjusted to a value of 1.0: epiproct 0.82 : cerci 0.69 : paraprocts 1.0.

Measurements (in mm): ( exuviae N = 6 , larvae N = 9 ): Total length (including appendages), exuviae 42.0– 46.5 , larvae 37.5 –41.0; abdomen length (ventral), exuviae 29– 32.5 , larvae 25.0–28.0; maximum width of head 8.7–9.4 ; hind femur (dorsal) 6.8–7.5 . Lateral spines on abdominal segments 6–9 (S 6 –S 9 ; measured in ventral view as shown in
Fig. 11
): on S 6 , 0.63–0.75 ; on S 7 , 0.98–1.22 ; on S 8 , 1.09–1.42 ; on S 9 , 0.86–1.09 . Caudal appendages (dorsal): epiproct 3.57 –4.00; cerci 2.86–3.41 ; paraprocts 4.2–4.9 .
